&lt;h2&gt;About the Role&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Abnormal AI is looking for a &lt;strong&gt;Content Strategist&lt;/strong&gt; to join our Content Marketing team and help connect messaging to activation across the business. This role sits at the intersection of campaign strategy, content development, and amplification: you’ll partner with Integrated Marketing and Content Marketing leadership to support campaign messaging, contribute to downstream execution, and help ensure content across channels is cohesive and ready for market.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is an individual contributor role for someone who is excited to operate in an AI-native environment. You’ll help take raw inputs — including research, customer stories, webinars, and internal materials — and turn them into activation-ready content and derivative assets using modern tools and workflows.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You’ll work across Product Marketing, Integrated Marketing, Social, Editorial, Brand/Creative, and other stakeholders to help Abnormal move faster and get more value from the content we create.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;What you will do&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with Integrated Marketing and Content Marketing leadership to support campaign messaging and downstream execution&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute to campaign execution across priority initiatives, helping maintain consistency as messaging is translated into emails, landing pages, social copy, webinars, and other assets&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build familiarity with the company’s campaigns and messaging, and help help maintain alignment with campaign messaging across outputs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Review and adapt content across formats to support repackaging and downstream use&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Translate raw inputs — including research, customer stories, internal podcasts, webinars, threat reports, and internal conversations — into activation-ready content and narrative outputs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify opportunities to extend the value of existing content by creating derivative assets (e.g., summaries, slides, clips, videos, or industry-specific cutdowns)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Help turn existing content and moments into amplification opportunities, including web experiences, campaign packages, contributed content, podcast pitches, and other distribution plays&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Use AI-assisted workflows to accelerate ideation, distillation, repackaging, and content transformation, while applying editorial judgment to refine outputs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute to building lightweight workflows for slicing, packaging, and distributing content more efficiently across channels&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Operate as a flexible generalist, contributing across a range of content and campaign needs with guidance from Content Marketing leadership&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Must Haves&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;2–4+ years of experience in B2B SaaS, cybersecurity, content marketing, or related roles&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong writing and editing fundamentals, with the ability to turn complex ideas into clear and concise content&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience or strong interest in using AI tools (e.g., ChatGPT, Claude) to create, transform, or repurpose content&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to work across multiple projects and stakeholders in a fast-moving environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Willingness to learn, iterate quickly, and adapt to new tools and workflows&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong attention to detail and a bias toward action&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborative mindset and openness to feedback&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Nice to Haves&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience supporting integrated marketing or campaign-based work&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with content operations tools (Asana, CMS platforms)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience creating derivative content formats (e.g., clips, summaries, presentations, or multimedia assets)&lt;/li&gt;
